Should I take the leap♪

2
00:00:39,270 --> 00:00:43,360
♪I'm tangled in the words
I meant to say♪

3
00:00:43,360 --> 00:00:47,808
♪Facing the towering skyscrapers ahead♪

4
00:00:47,940 --> 00:00:49,824
♪Should I lower my head and crawl♪

5
00:00:49,824 --> 00:00:51,776
♪Or keep climbing upward♪

6
00:00:52,064 --> 00:00:56,288
♪You never once slowed your pace♪

7
00:00:56,384 --> 00:00:59,410
♪You fear time will evaporate♪

8
00:01:00,900 --> 00:01:05,190
♪Engaging with the world
comes at a price♪

9
00:01:05,190 --> 00:01:06,304
♪Take the field immediately♪

10
00:01:06,304 --> 00:01:09,824
♪Why so many useless words♪

11
00:01:11,700 --> 00:01:12,940
♪Just right now♪

12
00:01:13,110 --> 00:01:15,740
♪Your dreams will come true♪

13
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:17,824
♪My accent is quirky♪

14
00:01:17,824 --> 00:01:20,260
♪Not standard Mandarin♪

15
00:01:20,370 --> 00:01:21,690
♪Just right now♪

16
00:01:21,690 --> 00:01:24,512
♪Time will speak your truth aloud♪

17
00:01:24,690 --> 00:01:26,848
♪No time gap between tomorrow and I♪

18
00:01:26,848 --> 00:01:29,010
♪Tears are blossoming♪

19
00:01:29,010 --> 00:01:31,110
♪The path of hope never divides♪

20
00:01:31,110 --> 00:01:33,280
♪Waiting for sunlight's embrace♪

21
00:01:36,570 --> 00:01:38,240
♪Just right now♪

22
00:01:38,670 --> 00:01:40,030
♪Take the field immediately♪

23
00:01:40,798 --> 00:01:44,015
=All Rise=

24
00:01:45,128 --> 00:01:47,656
=Episode 12=

25
00:01:49,032 --> 00:01:50,024
(Talent Hunt Program Day 43)

26
00:01:50,024 --> 00:01:51,944
(Jiang Chen 4, Huang Yue 3, Li Ke 3)

27
00:01:51,944 --> 00:01:53,992
(Yan Fei 2, Guo Xiaoyu 2, Ren Jiatong 1)

28
00:01:54,600 --> 00:01:55,401
Good dog.

29
00:01:56,681 --> 00:01:58,600
Miss, what's your dog's name?

30
00:01:59,240 --> 00:02:00,641
(Yong'an Noodle Shop)
We haven't named it yet.

31
00:02:01,761 --> 00:02:03,201
Why don't you give it a name?

32
00:02:05,520 --> 00:02:06,681
How about Chen?

33
00:02:11,720 --> 00:02:12,320
Chen.

34
00:02:12,600 --> 00:02:14,401
So you really don't like eggs at all?

35
00:02:22,121 --> 00:02:22,856
Want to hug it?

36
00:02:25,320 --> 00:02:26,081
I don't like dogs.

37
00:02:29,920 --> 00:02:31,440
It doesn't even move. So calm.

38
00:02:34,920 --> 00:02:35,640
It's so sweet.

39
00:02:35,640 --> 00:02:37,521
Let's call it "Sweetie" then.

40
00:02:42,320 --> 00:02:43,281
Sweetie?

41
00:02:50,880 --> 00:02:52,561
Want to try petting it?

42
00:03:04,281 --> 00:03:04,961
Sweetie.

43
00:03:07,681 --> 00:03:08,200
Okay.

44
00:03:10,401 --> 00:03:11,160
"Sweetie" it is.

45
00:03:13,128 --> 00:03:14,561
(Yong'an Noodle Shop)

46
00:03:14,561 --> 00:03:15,760
The rain stopped.

47
00:03:16,961 --> 00:03:17,880
Go to sleep.

48
00:03:37,561 --> 00:03:38,081
Mr. Zhou.

49
00:03:38,600 --> 00:03:39,320
Want a ride?

50
00:03:39,600 --> 00:03:40,841
No need, it's out of your way.

51
00:03:41,001 --> 00:03:41,961
The subway station

52
00:03:41,961 --> 00:03:42,600
is right ahead.

53
00:03:45,841 --> 00:03:46,480
What's wrong?

54
00:03:47,160 --> 00:03:48,841
Are you scared of my brother or me?

55
00:04:07,561 --> 00:04:08,480
Yan Fei, listen.

56
00:04:09,401 --> 00:04:10,121
I'm not scared of

57
00:04:10,121 --> 00:04:11,001
either of you.

58
00:04:11,720 --> 00:04:12,920
He didn't pressure me.

59
00:04:13,241 --> 00:04:14,880
He's not some tycoon in the novel.

60
00:04:14,880 --> 00:04:16,121
He can't tell me what to do.

61
00:04:16,801 --> 00:04:18,280
He sent someone to me because

62
00:04:18,960 --> 00:04:20,080
he cared about you.

63
00:04:22,440 --> 00:04:23,048
My girlfri...

64
00:04:23,440 --> 00:04:24,161
My ex-girlfriend

65
00:04:25,121 --> 00:04:26,200
caused us

66
00:04:26,241 --> 00:04:27,440
so much trouble at work.

67
00:04:27,880 --> 00:04:29,241
You think she didn't know

68
00:04:29,241 --> 00:04:30,520
right from wrong?

69
00:04:31,001 --> 00:04:33,320
No, she did it because
she's Liang Xiaosong's sister.

70
00:04:33,760 --> 00:04:35,400
She was trying her best to protect

71
00:04:35,400 --> 00:04:36,001
her brother.

72
00:04:36,080 --> 00:04:37,064
Your brother's the same.

73
00:04:37,320 --> 00:04:38,361
No matter what he does,

74
00:04:39,121 --> 00:04:40,481
he's trying to protect you.

75
00:04:42,161 --> 00:04:42,760
I don't know

76
00:04:42,760 --> 00:04:43,960
what your family is like.

77
00:04:44,241 --> 00:04:46,001
Your brother's only four or five years

78
00:04:46,640 --> 00:04:47,801
older than me,

79
00:04:48,080 --> 00:04:49,840
and he's carried Xingke alone for years.

80
00:04:50,481 --> 00:04:51,640
Business isn't easy now.

81
00:04:51,921 --> 00:04:53,001
You get to

82
00:04:53,640 --> 00:04:54,440
chase your dreams

83
00:04:54,561 --> 00:04:56,400
without worries at Jun An.

84
00:04:57,200 --> 00:04:57,960
But him?

85
00:04:58,440 --> 00:05:00,241
He might never even get a choice.

86
00:05:01,280 --> 00:05:02,400
Doesn't he have a dream?

87
00:05:08,041 --> 00:05:09,080
Most of our generation

88
00:05:10,161 --> 00:05:11,681
are only children.

89
00:05:12,001 --> 00:05:13,161
I envy those of you

90
00:05:13,161 --> 00:05:14,760
with siblings.

91
00:05:14,760 --> 00:05:16,320
After all, I wish someone

92
00:05:16,320 --> 00:05:17,721
could share my burdens too.

93
00:05:18,001 --> 00:05:18,536
Right?

94
00:05:19,001 --> 00:05:20,361
So forget about the ride.

95
00:05:20,801 --> 00:05:21,640
Go home and talk

96
00:05:22,121 --> 00:05:22,801
to your brother,

97
00:05:23,320 --> 00:05:23,944
okay?

98
00:05:25,608 --> 00:05:26,441
Well.

99
00:05:51,760 --> 00:05:53,681
It's karma for bullying me all the time.

100
00:05:53,760 --> 00:05:54,640
Caught a cold, huh?

101
00:05:55,121 --> 00:05:56,840
There's a reason for this.

102
00:05:57,001 --> 00:05:57,921
Reflect on it.

103
00:05:59,161 --> 00:06:01,241
Ask the housekeeper to cook for you

104
00:06:01,640 --> 00:06:02,520
if you're hungry.

105
00:06:03,001 --> 00:06:04,280
I'm too tired to argue.

106
00:06:04,840 --> 00:06:06,280
My head's pounding from meetings.

107
00:06:08,440 --> 00:06:10,681
All you do is work

108
00:06:10,681 --> 00:06:11,921
and have meetings.

109
00:06:12,440 --> 00:06:13,361
What's the point?

110
00:06:16,440 --> 00:06:17,241
This is life,

111
00:06:18,241 --> 00:06:19,241
even if it's pointless.

112
00:06:21,721 --> 00:06:23,241
Will you attend the meetings for me?

113
00:06:23,561 --> 00:06:24,121
No way.

114
00:06:26,200 --> 00:06:26,888
Yan Da.

115
00:06:27,921 --> 00:06:30,080
If you hadn't become Xingke's boss,

116
00:06:30,520 --> 00:06:31,241
what'd you do?

117
00:06:36,760 --> 00:06:38,200
What are you plotting?

118
00:06:39,361 --> 00:06:40,400
Just chitchatting.

119
00:06:41,320 --> 00:06:43,001
How old were you when you joined Xingke?

120
00:06:47,520 --> 00:06:48,161
Twenty-eight.

121
00:06:49,640 --> 00:06:50,481
You were a freshman.

122
00:06:51,960 --> 00:06:52,721
I got into

123
00:06:53,121 --> 00:06:55,121
a sociology PhD program in the UK.

124
00:06:56,681 --> 00:06:57,960
I meant to go abroad with you,

125
00:06:58,721 --> 00:06:59,960
but then Dad fell ill,

126
00:07:01,561 --> 00:07:02,440
so I didn't go.

127
00:07:05,320 --> 00:07:06,041
Doesn't matter.

128
00:07:07,080 --> 00:07:09,241
I wouldn't have become
some great scholar anyway.

129
00:07:10,921 --> 00:07:11,440
Someone

130
00:07:12,320 --> 00:07:14,601
in the family
had to shoulder the burdens.

131
00:07:17,200 --> 00:07:18,520
That must have been

132
00:07:19,400 --> 00:07:20,801
really tough for you.

133
00:07:22,801 --> 00:07:24,456
I hate it when you interfere in my life.

134
00:07:24,801 --> 00:07:26,561
But someone said you were protecting me.

135
00:07:28,161 --> 00:07:29,440
Actually, I know

136
00:07:29,721 --> 00:07:31,440
you've been making decisions

137
00:07:31,440 --> 00:07:32,801
for me to protect me.

138
00:07:35,681 --> 00:07:37,561
I'll forget about what happened today.

139
00:07:38,241 --> 00:07:38,921
But

140
00:07:39,361 --> 00:07:40,520
promise me.

141
00:07:40,880 --> 00:07:42,880
Ask me for help if anything happens

142
00:07:42,880 --> 00:07:44,361
at home

143
00:07:44,840 --> 00:07:45,960
or in our company.

144
00:07:47,400 --> 00:07:49,241
You might look down on law graduates,

145
00:07:49,640 --> 00:07:50,880
but I'm your sister.

146
00:07:50,880 --> 00:07:51,640
I'm also a Yan.

147
00:07:51,640 --> 00:07:52,561
I'm not useless.

148
00:07:52,561 --> 00:07:53,481
I'm pretty capable.

149
00:07:56,840 --> 00:07:57,400
Fei.

150
00:07:58,721 --> 00:07:59,440
What happened?

151
00:08:02,121 --> 00:08:03,400
You don't sound

152
00:08:03,840 --> 00:08:04,880
like yourself.

153
00:08:08,080 --> 00:08:09,561
I'm getting deeply moved.

154
00:08:11,241 --> 00:08:12,440
Should I burst into tears

155
00:08:12,880 --> 00:08:13,561
right now?

156
00:08:16,840 --> 00:08:17,960
Have you lost it?

157
00:08:18,361 --> 00:08:20,280
You just can't take sincere words.

158
00:08:26,280 --> 00:08:27,001
Are you hungry?

159
00:08:27,561 --> 00:08:28,200
No.

160
00:08:31,320 --> 00:08:32,481
"I don't like dogs."

161
00:08:32,481 --> 00:08:34,280
You almost took Sweetie home.

162
00:08:37,280 --> 00:08:39,280
Actually, I had a dog when I was young.

163
00:08:41,081 --> 00:08:42,920
But after my parents divorced,

164
00:08:44,481 --> 00:08:46,321
my dad gave it away.

165
00:08:48,680 --> 00:08:50,241
I remember how heartbroken I was.

166
00:08:50,241 --> 00:08:51,400
I cried so much.

167
00:08:51,400 --> 00:08:53,601
I kept begging him,
"Don't send Sweetie away.

168
00:08:53,601 --> 00:08:54,601
Don't send Sweetie away."

169
00:08:54,880 --> 00:08:55,880
He wouldn't listen.

170
00:08:56,680 --> 00:08:58,001
I don't know where he sent it.

171
00:08:59,841 --> 00:09:01,321
It was also called Sweetie?

172
00:09:04,800 --> 00:09:06,760
I named it randomly. What a coincidence.

173
00:09:08,721 --> 00:09:09,680
After that,

174
00:09:09,680 --> 00:09:11,001
I've developed

175
00:09:11,816 --> 00:09:12,400
PTSD

176
00:09:12,400 --> 00:09:13,441
with dogs.

177
00:09:14,800 --> 00:09:16,001
Even at that moment,

178
00:09:16,601 --> 00:09:17,800
my dad made sure

179
00:09:18,040 --> 00:09:18,721
to lecture me.

180
00:09:19,241 --> 00:09:21,400
"If you can't take care of someone,

181
00:09:22,040 --> 00:09:23,040
don't selfishly

182
00:09:23,040 --> 00:09:24,121
keep them around.

183
00:09:24,800 --> 00:09:26,520
You want to look after Sweetie? Fine.

184
00:09:26,800 --> 00:09:28,001
Gain power first."

185
00:09:30,241 --> 00:09:30,760
Well said.

186
00:09:31,721 --> 00:09:33,481
As expected of lawyer Jiang Ruocheng.

187
00:09:35,361 --> 00:09:36,560
You know how old I was?

188
00:09:37,280 --> 00:09:38,321
How could I gain power?

189
00:09:41,001 --> 00:09:41,760
A decade later,

190
00:09:41,760 --> 00:09:43,601
you're rubbing salt in my wounds here.

191
00:09:45,280 --> 00:09:46,081
I'm sorry.

192
00:09:47,321 --> 00:09:49,601
You didn't join
your dad's law firm because

193
00:09:49,601 --> 00:09:51,201
you disagreed with his principles?

194
00:09:52,721 --> 00:09:53,520
Kind of.

195
00:09:55,400 --> 00:09:56,040
He doesn't

196
00:09:57,560 --> 00:09:58,920
think much of me, saying that

197
00:09:59,841 --> 00:10:01,280
I'm not cut out to be a lawyer.

198
00:10:01,601 --> 00:10:02,441
That only makes me

199
00:10:02,760 --> 00:10:03,841
determined to prove

200
00:10:04,081 --> 00:10:05,361
that I could study,

201
00:10:05,640 --> 00:10:06,721
get into Haryald,

202
00:10:06,841 --> 00:10:07,841
and stay at Jun An.

203
00:10:08,241 --> 00:10:09,001
I could even...

204
00:10:12,280 --> 00:10:13,241
What?

205
00:10:14,201 --> 00:10:14,880
Outdo him?

206
00:10:16,201 --> 00:10:16,800
Defeat him?

207
00:10:17,241 --> 00:10:18,520
Fishing for information?

208
00:10:19,040 --> 00:10:20,400
Why am I the only one talking?

209
00:10:21,280 --> 00:10:21,960
What about you?

210
00:10:22,841 --> 00:10:23,361
Me?

211
00:10:32,880 --> 00:10:33,721
Are you a child?

212
00:10:34,241 --> 00:10:35,001
Want to try?

213
00:10:35,361 --> 00:10:36,008
No.

214
00:10:36,241 --> 00:10:37,280
It's stress-relieving.

215
00:10:37,361 --> 00:10:37,920
No.

216
00:10:38,520 --> 00:10:39,080
Seriously.

217
00:10:41,520 --> 00:10:43,560
I said no. I refused.

218
00:10:44,601 --> 00:10:45,201
Just try it.

219
00:10:46,696 --> 00:10:50,376
♪There's a place in my life♪

220
00:10:50,376 --> 00:10:53,896
♪And I want you to take it now♪

221
00:10:54,568 --> 00:10:58,280
♪Someday you'll be mine♪

222
00:10:58,280 --> 00:11:02,408
♪And we'll fly all over the world♪

223
00:11:02,856 --> 00:11:03,720
♪Don't you see♪

224
00:11:03,720 --> 00:11:06,760
♪My heart is beating fast♪

225
00:11:06,760 --> 00:11:07,656
♪And I know♪

226
00:11:07,656 --> 00:11:10,760
♪It will for a long long time♪

227
00:11:10,760 --> 00:11:12,200
♪You're the one I need♪

228
00:11:12,200 --> 00:11:16,168
♪Because you make me feel so alright♪

229
00:11:18,568 --> 00:11:22,120
♪You're looking for some honesty♪

230
00:11:22,632 --> 00:11:26,536
♪And for someone you could understand♪

231
00:11:26,536 --> 00:11:28,232
♪All you have to do♪

232
00:11:28,232 --> 00:11:32,136
♪Is let me love you by yourself♪

233
00:11:33,864 --> 00:11:37,416
♪Some say love is blind♪

234
00:11:37,512 --> 00:11:38,568
♪But we know♪

235
00:11:38,568 --> 00:11:40,904
♪This one is so true♪

236
00:11:41,800 --> 00:11:45,480
♪The sun shines so bright♪

237
00:11:46,440 --> 00:11:49,960
(Yan Fei: Thanks for your advice.
Things are fine.)

238
00:11:50,184 --> 00:11:53,448
(Zhou Nian: Made peace with him?
He won't interfere anymore?)

239
00:11:54,664 --> 00:11:56,872
(Yan Fei: Not really. It's just...
Things are fine.)

240
00:11:59,208 --> 00:12:02,376
(Yan Fei: Anyway, thanks,
management guru.)

241
00:12:05,832 --> 00:12:09,352
♪You're looking for some honesty♪

242
00:12:09,768 --> 00:12:13,736
♪And for someone you could understand♪

243
00:12:13,736 --> 00:12:15,400
♪All you have to do♪

244
00:12:15,400 --> 00:12:19,112
♪Is let me love you by yourself♪

245
00:12:22,441 --> 00:12:23,361
Jiatong, you're back?

246
00:12:24,001 --> 00:12:24,640
Have you eaten?

247
00:12:25,841 --> 00:12:26,560
Yeah.

248
00:12:28,280 --> 00:12:29,880
Something amazing happened.

249
00:12:30,441 --> 00:12:30,961
You know?

250
00:12:31,400 --> 00:12:33,640
I always thought
I had great people skills.

251
00:12:34,040 --> 00:12:35,920
Being likable is what I've excelled at

252
00:12:35,920 --> 00:12:36,961
for twenty whole years.

253
00:12:37,481 --> 00:12:38,601
But today I met this lady,

254
00:12:38,920 --> 00:12:40,121
the one Yan Fei pissed off.

255
00:12:40,760 --> 00:12:42,121
The residents' committee staff

256
00:12:42,481 --> 00:12:44,880
said her husband
got injured during his commute.

257
00:12:45,160 --> 00:12:47,040
I was about to raise funds for her.

258
00:12:47,721 --> 00:12:48,920
But Mr. Zhou told me

259
00:12:49,280 --> 00:12:50,560
that we must treat

260
00:12:50,680 --> 00:12:51,520
the clients

261
00:12:51,721 --> 00:12:53,481
who are relatively disadvantaged

262
00:12:53,560 --> 00:12:54,201
with empathy,

263
00:12:54,520 --> 00:12:55,680
but not sympathy.

264
00:12:56,160 --> 00:12:58,241
I shouldn't judge others from

265
00:12:58,321 --> 00:12:59,520
a privileged standpoint.

266
00:12:59,721 --> 00:13:00,880
That's disrespectful.

267
00:13:01,601 --> 00:13:03,280
Guo Xiaoyu, you've really changed.

268
00:13:03,800 --> 00:13:05,081
You used to nag me

269
00:13:05,081 --> 00:13:06,721
about Zhubao all day.

270
00:13:06,800 --> 00:13:08,201
Now all you talk about is work.

271
00:13:09,040 --> 00:13:09,672
Really?

272
00:13:22,001 --> 00:13:22,760
Maybe it's because

273
00:13:23,920 --> 00:13:25,441
things are over between us.

274
00:13:28,920 --> 00:13:29,800
Forget it.

275
00:13:29,841 --> 00:13:31,121
Work keeps me busy.

276
00:13:31,760 --> 00:13:32,560
But at night,

277
00:13:33,841 --> 00:13:36,280
I feel completely hollowed out inside.

278
00:13:37,560 --> 00:13:38,728
Don't even wanna watch shows.

279
00:13:43,160 --> 00:13:44,361
Did he contact you?

280
00:13:47,160 --> 00:13:48,241
But I think he will.

281
00:13:49,920 --> 00:13:50,800
Our last fight

282
00:13:50,800 --> 00:13:52,040
lasted even longer than this.

283
00:13:53,121 --> 00:13:55,001
It's just about who caves in first.

284
00:13:55,560 --> 00:13:56,640
It's a mind game right now.

285
00:13:56,800 --> 00:13:59,280
Whoever surrenders first
will have to submit to the other.

286
00:13:59,680 --> 00:14:00,721
